PUBLIC TRANSPORTATION IS STRONGLY RECOMMENDED! 
(For Public Transportation information, call 511) 

From the North (Marin, Sonoma, Napa, and Mendocino Counties): 
s Take the 101 Freeway South across the Golden Gate Bridge. 
s Follow 101 South, through the city, and then back onto the freeway. 
s Follow to the 3Com Park exit. 
s Follow the signs to the park. 

From the Northeast (Solano, Yolo, and Sacramento Counties): 
s Take Interstate 80 West, across the Bay Bridge, to the 101 
freeway South. 
s Take the 3Com Park exit 
s Follow the signs to the park. 

From the East (Northern Alameda and Contra Costa Counties): 
s Take the Bay Bridge (Interstate 80) West, to the 101 freeway South. 
s Take the 3Com Park exit, and follow signs to the park. 

From the Southeast (Southern Alameda County): 
s Take either the Dumbarton or San Mateo Bridge to the 101 freeway North. 
s Take the 3Com Park exit, and follow signs to the park. 

From the South (Northeastern San Mateo, Santa Clara and Monterey Counties): 
s Take the 101 freeway North to the 3Com Park exit. 
s Follow the signs to the park. 

From the Southwest (Northwestern and Southern San Mateo County): 
s Take Interstate 280 North to the 101 freeway South. 
s Take the 3Com Park exit and follow the signs to the park.

venue.rules:
PERMITTED & PROHIBITED ITEMS 

ALL INDIVIDUALS ENTERING THE STADIUM WILL BE SUBJECT TO SEARCH. THE FOLLOWING INFORMATION IS SUBJECT TO CHANGE WITHOUT NOTICE. 

Fans with medical bags or items they must carry with them must be inspected and either have a wristband or sticker placed on it to show that it has been inspected. 

The following items ARE permitted in the stadium during Forty Niners games: 


The following items *ARE* permitted during 49er games:
* Small purses or fanny packs measuring less than 14" x 14" x 4"
* Plastic grocery-type bags and/or clear plastic zip-lock bags
* Seat cushions approximately 14" x 14" x 4"
* Plastic bottles (sealed) and thermoses (no alcohol)
* Cameras and video equipment (no lights, tripods, or monopods)
* Food and fruit (must be cut into pieces)
* Flags (No poles)
The following items *ARE NOT* permitted in the stadium:
* Bags (including but not limited to opaque, duffel and sports bags) measuring more than 14"x14"x4"
* Coolers and backpacks
* Large purses & fanny packs larger than 14"x14"x4"
* Weapons of any kind (including silverware)
* Cans, glass bottles or alcoholic beverages
* Klaxons, bullhorns, whistles or any other noisemakers
* Laser pointers of any type
* Signs, banners or poles
* Any fan perceived to be intoxicated
* Smoking (except in designated areas)
* Projectiles (footballs, Frisbees, etc.)
Anyone possessing these items will be asked to return them to their cars or dispose of them in the garbage cans provided at the gates.
FOR CONCERTS:
* NO cans or bottles (of any kind including plastic
* NO alcohol
* NO taping equipment, videos, cameras
* NO weapons of any kind
* NO lawn chairs
* NO ice chests
* NO umbrellas
* NO frisbees or projectiles
